.TH PORTWHO 1 "February 2026" "portwho 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
portwho \- show which process is listening on a TCP/UDP port
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B portwho
.I <port>
.br
.B portwho
.B --kill
.I <port>
.br
.B portwho
.B --help
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B portwho
prints listener details for a port on Linux. It prefers
.B ss
and falls back to
.B lsof
when needed.
.PP
With
.B --kill
it asks for confirmation and then sends SIGTERM to matching process IDs.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B <port>
Port number from 1 to 65535.
.TP
.B --kill <port>
Enable kill mode with confirmation prompt.
.TP
.B -h, --help
Show help.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Kill mode failed to resolve safe PID candidates.
.TP
.B 2
Invalid usage or invalid port.
.SH AUTHOR
Mohitul Islam <connect@mohitul-islam.com>
.SH HOMEPAGE
